      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix, knead, and bulk ferment, 1 hour",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix {{strong-bread-flour}}, {{yeast-fast-action}}, {{salt-table}}, and {{caster-sugar}}. Add the {{whole-milk}}, {{water}}, and {{unsalted-butter}} and bring together. Knead for 8 to 10 minutes until smooth and elastic. Place in an oiled bowl, cover, and leave until doubled, about 1 hour.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape and prove, 40 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide into 8 equal pieces. Shape each into a sausage about 12 cm long, tapering the ends slightly. Arrange in a row on a lined tray, touching, with the long sides together. Cover and prove for 40 minutes until puffed. Heat the oven to 190°C (170°C fan).",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Brush with milk or beaten egg. Bake for 14 to 16 minutes until light golden. The undersides should be pale gold, not deep brown, these are soft buns, not crusty rolls. Cool on a rack. Once cool, split each bun down the top with a serrated knife, cutting three-quarters of the way through.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
